Mike,
Bad tire wear on the inside could also be due to a bent tie rod. Before you
shell out the big bux on ball joints and steering box, you may want to start
with new tires, new tie rods, new drag link and an alignment at a shop that
knows busses, but bring them your Bentley anyways.

